text: The County of London was a county of England from 1889 to 1965, corresponding to the area today known as Inner London. It was created as part of the general introduction of elected county government in England, by way of the Local Government Act 1888. ==Other websites== *County of London boundary map Category:Local government in London Category:1889 establishments in England Category:1965 disestablishments in England Category:19th century in London Category:20th century in London
